class.rdfs:comment: A DeliveryTimeSettings represents re-usable pieces of shipping information, relating to timing. It is designed for publication on an URL that may be referenced via the shippingSettingsLink property of a OfferShippingSpecification. Several occurrences can be published, distinguished (and identified/referenced) by their different values for shippingLabel.
class.rdfs:label: DeliveryTimeSettings

schema:deliveryTime.rdfs:comment: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.
schema:deliveryTime.rdfs:label: deliveryTime

schema:shippingDestination.rdfs:comment: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways e.g. postalCode ranges.
schema:shippingDestination.rdfs:label: shippingDestination

schema:transitTimeLabel.rdfs:comment: Label to match an OfferShippingDetails with a DeliveryTimeSettings (within the context of a shippingSettingsLink cross-reference).
schema:transitTimeLabel.rdfs:label: transitTimeLabel
